# Environment Variables for Streamer Theme
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your actual values

# AWS Configuration (for Parameter Store)
# Option 1: Use AWS credentials directly (not recommended for production)
# VITE_AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your_aws_access_key_id
# VITE_AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your_aws_secret_access_key

# AWS Region (defaults to us-east-1 if not set)
# VITE_AWS_REGION=us-east-1

# For development, you can override the default configuration
# Note: These values will be public in the browser, so don't put sensitive data here
# VITE_TWITCH_USERNAME=your_channel_name

# Production Settings
# In production, use IAM roles instead of hardcoded credentials
# Set up AWS Parameter Store with these parameters:
# - /twitch/client-id (your Twitch Client ID)
# - /twitch/access-token (your Twitch Access Token - use SecureString type)

# Development Mode
# If you want to test without AWS Parameter Store, you can temporarily
# hardcode values in the config.ts file, but don't commit them!
